main event: A military observer reported seeing a fast-moving object over the Canal Zone, Panama on March 7, 1953.
interesting points: The object was observed for an unspecified length of time.
The object's course was not reported.
No photographs were taken of the object.
Physical evidence of the object was reported, but no further details are provided.
The conclusion was that the object was unidentified, possibly a small object at high altitude or a meteor.
